<div id='gazette_story'>
    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>One Fun Summer Thus Far...</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20100729.png' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, July 29, 2010</b> &mdash;
    Mayor Wright addressed his audience in golden slippers. &quot;I won these slippers at the <a href="http://millsberry.com/greenhouse/index.phtml"><i>Honey Nut Cheerios&reg;  Greenhouse</i></a> Buzz the Bee picked them out for me in the Prize Hive,&quot; Wright chuckled.<br><br>The <a href="http://millsberry.com/greenhouse/index.phtml"><i>Greenhouse</i></a> is great to visit any time, but its offerings make up just a small portion of the exciting happenings going on in Millsberry this summer. And now, with a new month upon us, the mayor said he wanted to take a moment to talk about some of the newest additions to town.<br><br>Wright noted, &quot;In the beginning of June, <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=7">Trix, Toys, and Games</a>.  got a facelift. So, thanks to the fruity-delicious taste of <i>Trix&reg;</i> cereal, the store has been renamed and restocked. And that means everyone can escape to fantastical places thanks to fresh new murals--or get their fun on with the help of other cool items, like banana boats!&quot;<br>
<br>
The crowd cheered and a few even raised their Berry Blue Trix Swords up in the air in agreement.<br><br>Wright cheered too, adding, &quot;And then there&#039;s the <a href="http://millsberry.com/career_center"><i>Career Center</i></a>, challenging Millsberrians to try their hand at something new and get rewarded for it! I know it&#039;s a popular spot based on the number of new surfers and racecar drivers I&#039;ve been seeing around town! So, let&#039;s give a round of applause to Caroline Carrera for bringing this great venue to Millsberry.&quot;<br><br>The crowd cheered again and then let out a collective gasp. Chip the Wolf (the Cookie Crisp Cereal-loving wolf) was suddenly front and center in the crowd. A nervous silence hung in the air...until it was replaced by laughter when everyone realized it wasn&#039;t Chip, but a fellow citizen in a Chip costume!<br><br>The mayor then continued his speech, noting: &quot;Well, we still don&#039;t know if Chip is gone for good, especially since the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/ckcfactory/"><i>Cookie Crisp&reg; Cereal Factory</i></a> has settled here in town. We know Chip is tempted by this great-tasting breakfast cereal, so we thank you for your help in keeping the factory running at its full potential by playing the mini-games inside! Keep going back because you&#039;ll win some cool new items, too!&quot;<br><br>&quot;And, last but not least, I double-dare all of you to hop on one foot until I say &#039;stop.&#039;&quot;<br><br>The crowd obliged and Wright chuckled a bit before finally saying the magic word. &quot;As you can see, everyone loves a double dare and, because of the new <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/campaigns/frudare2010/">Double Dare Fruit Roll-Ups&reg; fruit-flavored snacks</a>, tons of you have been doing dares and getting rewarded for it! If you haven&#039;t already, get creative and think of a dare that could be printed on an actual Fruit Roll-Ups roll! Just don&#039;t submit &quot;hop on one foot&quot; because it&#039;s already been used! So thank you for a wonderful two months. This makes me one proud mayor!&quot;<br><br>So there you have it: the ingredients for one delicious summer...so far. With surprises like the ones discussed above, there&#039;s no telling what&#039;s in store for August!
    </div>

